        "subject": "LU-1158 general: remove obd_time typedef in lieu of __s64",
        "message": "LU-1158 general: remove obd_time typedef in lieu of __s64\n\nAs it became clear with the addition of separate nanosecond time\nfields that the old obd_time-type fields were to be used exclusively\nfor storing time in seconds, the obd_time type was removed in lieu of\nsimply explicitly using signed 64-bit integers for these fields.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Isami Romanowski <isami@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I9eab200443afc19eabdf79f1a888773e8262183e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
